The paper discusses the design of deep neural networks for highly resource-constrained devices, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on tasks such as auto-encoding and image classification, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach of discretizing network weights and activations is a technique used in neural network quantization (cs.NE), and the paper also discusses the use of bi-level weights and activations, which is a technique used in binary neural networks (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the need to simplify operations for efficient inference, which is a topic relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
